ar from the best of times.\", \"from\": 1438, \"to\": 1507, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1450, \"end\": 1468, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Conservative_Party_of_Canada\", \"score\": 0.9999999999949978, \"rank\": 5.034171715931383e-12, \"text\": \"Conservative Party\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Conservative_Party_of_Canada\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Conservative_Party_of_Canada\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"times\", \"from\": 1501, \"to\": 1506}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Following the general election, the Tories have been reduced to a rump of 121 MPs - but of course, they still need a leader.\", \"from\": 1509, \"to\": 1633, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1545, \"end\": 1551, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tory\", \"score\": 0.9999999996339284, \"rank\": 3.6608150287110126e-10, \"text\": \"Tories\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tory\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tory\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the general election\", \"from\": 1519, \"to\": 1539}, {\"ngram\": \"a rump\", \"from\": 1573, \"to\": 1579}, {\"ngram\": \"121 MPs\", \"from\": 1583, \"to\": 1590}, {\"ngram\": \"course\", \"from\": 1600, \"to\": 1606}, {\"ngram\": \"a leader\", \"from\": 1624, \"to\": 1632}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It would be easy to assume, given the state of Parliament and low esteem the last government was held in by the public, that the Conservatives have a free hit.\", \"from\": 1634, \"to\": 1793, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1681, \"end\": 1691, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Parliament_of_the_United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.99540897372039, \"rank\": 0.002312609908869858, \"text\": \"Parliament\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q11204\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Parliament_of_the_United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Parliament_of_the_United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 1763, \"end\": 1776, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Conservatism\", \"score\": 0.9526378557991465, \"rank\": 0.04022824781603597, \"text\": \"Conservatives\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Conservatism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Conservatism\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the state\", \"from\": 1668, \"to\": 1677}, {\"ngram\": \"low esteem\", \"from\": 1696, \"to\": 1706}, {\"ngram\": \"the last government\", \"from\": 1707, \"to\": 1726}, {\"ngram\": \"the public\", \"from\": 1742, \"to\": 1752}, {\"ngram\": \"a free hit\", \"from\": 1782, \"to\": 1792}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That the next leader has no chance of becoming prime minister.\", \"from\": 1794, \"to\": 1856, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the next leader\", \"from\": 1799, \"to\": 1814}, {\"ngram\": \"no chance\", \"from\": 1819, \"to\": 1828}, {\"ngram\": \"prime minister\", \"from\": 1841, \"to\": 1855}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Yet this would be to ignore the growing volatility of British politics.\", \"from\": 1857, \"to\": 1928, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1911, \"end\": 1918, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9999917916343668, \"rank\": 4.892301205025282e-06, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the growing volatility\", \"from\": 1885, \"to\": 1907}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If Labour can go from Jeremy Corbyn to Downing Street in less than five years, there is no reason why the Tories cannot tread a similar path.\", \"from\": 1929, \"to\": 2070, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1932, \"end\": 1938, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_Labour_Party\", \"score\": 0.8775470460639719, \"rank\": 0.13355883814919406, \"text\": \"Labour\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand